{"blocks":[{"key":"crom8","text":"On Day 0, check iPSCs to see if they are ~100% confluent. Aspirate iPSC media and wash cells one with 2ml PBS (ThermoFisher Gibco) per well. Then add 5ml of \"Media A\" to each 6-well plate to initiate differentiation. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":157,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5apff","text":"On Day 3, aspirate media and replace with fresh 5ml of \"Media B\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":55,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2o86f","text":"On Day 2, prepare \"Media B\" which consists of:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":18,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"r4fm","text":"50ml N2B27","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c0e3r","text":"2uM Dorsomorphin (Tocris 3093/10) ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"397jv","text":"5uM SB 431542 (Tocris 1614/10)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4v1j9","text":"1uM CHIR99021 (Miltenyi Biotec 130-104-172)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9jr60","text":"1uM Purmorphamine (Merck Millipore SML0868)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6eeaq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"53t79","text":"Aspirate media and replace with 5ml of \"Media B\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7pvae","text":"On Day 1, aspirate media and replace with fresh 5ml of \"Media A\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":55,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5eov4","text":"On Day 8, prepare \"Media C\" which consists of:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":18,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4735t","text":"50ml N2B27","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6p8kn","text":"2uM Dorsomorphin (Tocris 3093/10) ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6plto","text":"1uM Purmorphamine (Merck Millipore SML0868)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"61ke8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dpp1g","text":"Aspirate media and replace with 5ml of \"Media C\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":39,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"28o6u","text":"On Day 5 till and including day 7 aspirate the media and replace with fresh 5ml of \"Media B\". Daily media change.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":83,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aqrjt","text":"On Day 4, split the cells in a 1:2 dilution following the \"Dispase protocol\" below, and plate the split cells into new Geltrex pre-coated 6-well plates in 2ml per well of \"Media B\" + 10μM Y-27632 dihydrochloride (Tocris). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":58,"length":18},{"style":"bold","offset":171,"length":40}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ab4lv","text":"On Day 14, split the cells in a 2:3 dilution following the \"Dispase protocol\" below, and plate the split cells into new Geltrex pre-coated 6-well plates in 2ml per well of just N2B27 + 10μM Y-27632 dihydrochloride (Tocris). At this point, NPCs can also be cryopreserved","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":59,"length":18},{"style":"bold","offset":177,"length":36}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fdogk","text":"On Day 11 till and including day 13 aspirate the media and replace with fresh 5ml of \"Media C\". Daily media change.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":85,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c6qcp","text":"On Day 10, split the cells in a 1:2 dilution following the \"Dispase protocol\" below, and plate the split cells into new Geltrex pre-coated 6-well plates in 2ml per well of \"Media C\" + 10μM Y-27632 dihydrochloride (Tocris).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":59,"length":18},{"style":"bold","offset":172,"length":40}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"evb4r","text":"On Day 9, aspirate media and replace with fresh 5ml of \"Media C\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":55,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"565hb","text":"On day 15, aspirate the media and replace with 5ml of N2B27. The cells are now midbrain NPCs, and media can be changed every 2 days until final plating.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":54,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1d6lt","text":"On day 19 prior to final plating, coat plates, ibidi chambers, 96-well plates, coverslips with Geltrex for final plating of NPCs for terminal differentiation into neurons. At this point, NPCs can also be cryopreserved","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ef54e","text":"Using Accutase (ThermoFisher Gibco), get cells into a single cell suspension and count the cells.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1dvqv","text":"Make up N2B27 + 10μM Y-27632 dihydrochloride to plate cells in.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9ptni","text":"Prepare cell stocks to obtain a final plating density of 500,000 cells per ml.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a48ct","text":"Plate the cells into final chambers: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b7l6b","text":"100,000 cells per well of a µ-Slide 8 Well (Ibidi chamber).","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8g8j5","text":"50,000 cells per well of a 96-well plate.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3io6q","text":"500,000 cells of a 12-well plate.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6u283","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6tiee","text":"On day 20, prepare Terminal Differentiation media:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"57u40","text":"50ml N2B27","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f237","text":"10μM Y-27632 dihydrochloride","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ha22","text":"0.1μM Compound E (Enzo Life Sciences).","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8lojd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fpfme","text":"Aspirate media and replace with \"Terminal Differentiation media\". ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":32,"length":34}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fchon","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6e9vu","text":"Cells need to be changed with Terminal Differentiation media twice weekly until desired differentiation time point (3-5 weeks).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"64f7o","text":"On the days indicated above, cells need to be enzymatically dissociated using Dispase. Before beginning coat 6-well plates with Geltrex. On day 4, and 10 cells are split 1:2 (1 well of a 6-well plate is split into 2 wells). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a86rs","text":"On day 14, cells are split 2:3 (2 wells of a 6-well plate are split into 3 wells).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a57g0","text":"Prepare dispase: Dissolve dispase powder in sterile PBS (ThermoFisher Gibco) to obtain a concentration of 1mg/ml. Make sure dispase is completely dissolved. Can increase speed of dissolving by shaking the falcon tube.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eegnp","text":"Filter the dissolved dispase in a sterile environment through a 0.22um filter.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"amacr","text":"Add a 1:10 dilution to each well of the 6-well plate containing the cells (500ul of dispase to each well containing 5ml of media).","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8b041","text":"Leave in the incubator for ~20 minutes checking the plate every 10 minutes.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"sure","text":"Whilst cells are in the dispase, add 10ml of sterile PBS to a 15ml falcon, 1 falcon for each iPSC line.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e60jh","text":"Add DNase I (Roche) to each falcon containing PBS to achieve a final concentration of 0.1mg/ml DNase I (stock is made up to be 10mg/ml). Add 100ul per falcon containing 10ml of PBS.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9k5uk","text":"Once cells have lifted (they should lift as a continuous sheet), add the cells to its respective 15ml falcon containing PBS and DNase I. Invert the falcon 2-3 times to break up, and wash the cells. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"676ie","text":"Allow the cells to settle to the bottom of the falcon with gravity flow.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"50vni","text":"Once they have settled, aspirate the PBS and 10ml of fresh sterile PBS to each falcon. Invert the falcon again 2-3 times to break up cells into smaller clumps.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"24eum","text":"Allow the cells to settle to the bottom of the falcon with gravity flow.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3hc1v","text":"In the meantime prepare the required media with the extra addition of 10μM Y-27632 dihydrochloride.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":70,"length":29}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4hods","text":"When cells have all settled to the bottom, aspirate the PBS and add the required amount of media to each falcon to achieve a final volume of 2ml per well of a 6-well plate (for eg. splitting 1 well into 2, the total will be 4ml in the falcon. 2ml will then be added to each well).","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e8r5h","text":"Pipette up and down using a 5ml stripette to break up clumps of cells.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"16pbo","text":"Add the cell suspension to the 6-well plate achieving the desired cell split. Move the cells in several quick side-to-side and back-and-forth motions to disperse the cells uniformly across the well. Place them in the incubator.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
